{
  "title": "About Rcnoutliner Plugin",
  "story": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "c7e4a913f2b8d046",
      "text": "The Rcnoutliner plugin embeds a hierarchical outliner directly in a wiki page. Create, edit, indent, and reorder nodes inline without leaving the wiki. Use it to capture structured thinking — agendas, plans, breakdowns, and outlines — as living wiki content."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "a1b2c3d4e5f60001",
      "text": "**Keyboard shortcuts:** **Enter** adds a sibling node below. **Tab** indents (makes the node a child of the one above). **Shift-Tab** outdents back to the parent's level. **F2** or **double-click** enters edit mode. **Escape** exits edit mode. **Delete** or **Backspace** on an empty node removes it. **Arrow Up / Down** navigate between nodes. Typing any printable character while a node is selected jumps directly into edit mode."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "9f2b6e7a3d1c8054",
      "text": "Click **MORE ↗** to open the full MORE Outliner in a popup window. MORE adds **Hoist** — focus on any subtree by making it the temporary root, hiding everything above it. Exports: **Markdown** (indented list), **HTML** (nested list), and **FedWiki ghost page** (sends the outline as a new page into the wiki lineup, with each top-level node as a paragraph). Changes made in MORE are saved back to the wiki item when you click Save."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "b2c3d4e5f6a70002",
      "text": "Outline content is autosaved to the wiki via FedWiki's native page API. The plugin works on any FedWiki instance — no local proxy or server required."
    },
    {
      "type": "rcnoutliner",
      "id": "5a3d8c1f4e9b7062",
      "text": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "1e6f9a4b2c7d3085",
      "text": "Developed by Marc Pierson with Claude Sonnet 4.6 (Anthropic) for the ReLocalize Creativity Network. Source: [[https://github.com/marpie1/wiki-plugin-rcnoutliner]]. Published on npm as wiki-plugin-rcnoutliner."
    }
  ],
